<div><h3>PHIL 240 - Epistemology </h3>  <hr>An examination of the nature of rationality and knowledge. Possible topics include (1) the problem of skepticism, (2) analyses of knowledge, (3) theories of justification, and (4) the central works in epistemology by significant figures &#8211; for example, Plato, Descartes, Hume, Kant, and Russell.<br><br><strong>Prerequisites:</strong> One course in philosophy.<br><br><strong>Anticipated Terms Offered:</strong> Offered periodically<br><br></div>		</td>
